# Local dev (dev-auth, Floci). Copy to .env and adjust for non-compose runs.
DROP_HTTP_PORT=8080
DROP_BASE_DOMAIN=drop.localhost
DROP_S3_BUCKET=drop-sites
DROP_S3_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4566
DROP_S3_REGION=us-east-1
DROP_S3_KEY_ID=test
DROP_S3_SECRET=test
DROP_DEV_AUTH=1

# Production (Google login) — leave DROP_DEV_AUTH unset/0 and set:
# DROP_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...apps.googleusercontent.com
# DROP_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# DROP_ALLOWED_DOMAINS=example.com
# DROP_S3_ENDPOINT=        # leave empty for real AWS S3

# Compute plane (container apps via POST /v1/apps). Opt-in: set DROP_KUBECONFIG to
# enable; without it the API is static-only and /v1/apps returns 501.
# DROP_KUBECONFIG=/home/you/.kube/drop-k3s.yaml
#
# Per-tenant egress isolation: in-cluster pod/service (+ control-plane) CIDRs that are
# EXCLUDED from the outbound-443 allowlist, so an app can't reach another tenant or the
# platform DB over 443. MUST cover the live pod+service CIDRs. Default 10.0.0.0/8 fits
# LOCAL k3s (pod 10.42/16, service 10.43/16). On EKS the pod/service CIDRs are often
# OUTSIDE 10/8 (e.g. 172.16/12, 100.64/10, service 172.20/16) — set the real ones or
# cross-tenant 443 egress is silently left open:
# DROP_BLOCKED_EGRESS_CIDRS=172.16.0.0/12,100.64.0.0/10,172.20.0.0/16
